SOCKS -D
-D port This works by allocating a socket to listen to port on the local side, and whenever
a connection is made to this port, the con- nection is forwarded over the secure channel,
and the applica- tion protocol is then used to determine where to connect to from the
remote machine. Currently the SOCKS4 and SOCKS5 protocols are supported, and ssh will act
as a SOCKS server. Only root can forward privileged ports. Dynamic port forwardings can
also be specified in the configuration file.
